==English==
===Etymology===
From the 19th century, to describe an earlier flag that incorportated a golden harp.  The term is still used informally even though the modern Irish flag is green, white and orange.

===Noun===
'''the green, white and gold''' ''or'' '''the Green, White and Gold'''

#(''informal'') The [[Irish]] [[flag]].

